{
  "title": "Capabilities",
  "description": "Frozen snapshot of host-environment feature support: which renderer backends are available, which input modalities are present, audio / fullscreen / vibration / OffscreenCanvas / Worker support, max touch points, and the resolved devicePixelRatio. Construction is private — the only public entry is Capabilities.ready, a lazy-cached `Promise<Capabilities>` that fires the (mostly) async probes on first access. The resolved instance is frozen and never mutates. Application.capabilities returns the same instance once `app.start()` has resolved.",
