          "name": "ready",
          "signature": "ready: Promise<Capabilities>",
          "params": [],
          "returnType": null,
          "description": "Lazy-cached Promise that resolves to a frozen Capabilities instance. The first read kicks off the async probes (currently just the WebGPU adapter request); every subsequent read returns the same Promise. Concurrent callers share the in-flight detection — no double work. Early-warmup pattern for callers who want to overlap detection with other startup work: ts void Capabilities.ready; // fire-and-forget; starts probes now // ... unrelated bootstrap ... const caps = await Capabilities.ready; // typically already resolved "
